author: CNET
description:
In case you didn’t know how to  level up your iPhone photography with RAW photos, CNET’s Managing Editor Patrick Holland will show you what to do. To start you’ll need to go to your Settings, then the Camera menu. Select Formats and turn on ProRAW & Resolution Control.

Once enabled, open the Camera app. If you're running iOS 26, you should see a button that says JPEG, HEIC or raw on the top left side. Tap on it to see controls for Format and Resolution. Raw images can be captured at 48MP on the iPhone 17 Pro. 

Stay tuned for more hidden iPhone tips. #ios26 #iphonephotography #iphone17pro #hiddeniphonetricks #rawphotos
title: iPhone 17 Hidden Tip: Use RAW Photos To Level Up Your iPhone Photography 📸🤳
